      "name": "Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Automate a multi-step process with HTTP / REST API and MySQL hands-free\n\n**Pattern:** Workflow Automation · **Level:** Advanced · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nAutomate a multi-step process with HTTP / REST API and MySQL hands-free. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual utilities is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nHourly Schedule → Load Previous Snapshot → Fetch Changes Since Watermark → Normalize Records → Upsert into Google Sheets → Advance Watermark → Persist Watermark (MySQL) → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to workflow automation without manual effort\n- Anyone automating utilities in productivity\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Saves hours of manual work each week\n- Scales without extra headcount\n- Removes copy-paste errors\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2 / service account; MySQL connection; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "ff3411e1-f060-0562-717b-6beca9120a84",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -20
      ],
      "id": "6ee5fa96-a5f3-d262-0e91-46d60686c330",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your utilities process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 4
      },
